    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Introduce a lightweight `tl.copy` implementation registry in the existing copy op files.\n- Move CUDA-specific copy lowering into `src/backend/cuda/op/copy.cc`.\n- Add CPU and ROCm copy implementations: CPU supports normal copy lowering, while ROCm supports normal and async copy lowering.\n- Add backend op source globs and a `src` include root so backend files can include headers from the source root.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `cmake -S . -B build`\n- `cmake --build build -j$(nproc)`\n- `python -m pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_copy.py -x`\n- `python -m pytest testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_lower_ptx_async_copy.py -x`\n- `python -m pytest testing/python/cpu/test_tilelang_cpu_gemm.py -x`\n- `python -m pytest testing/python/amd/test_tilelang_gfx950_copy_async.py -x -rs` (all skipped because ROCm support/device is unavailable in this environment)\n- `./format.sh` (pre-commit checks passed; the script returned non-zero because it detected unstaged local changes)\n- `clang-format --dry-run --Werror src/backend/cpu/op/copy.cc src/backend/cuda/op/copy.cc src/backend/rocm/op/copy.cc`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added CPU, CUDA, and ROCm copy backends with hardware-aware instruction selection, improved async/TMA handling, and layout-aware lowering for better performance.\n* **Refactor**\n  * Centralized copy lowering into a target-dispatch layer and added target-dispatch for Conv2D im2col lowering.\n* **Chores**\n  * Build configuration updated to discover and compile new backend operation sources.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
